Daily Dairy: Rules, Regulations, and Policies
This document outlines the official policies for the Daily Dairy application. These policies ensure a safe, secure, and transparent experience for all users.

1. Privacy Policy
Last Updated: May 7, 2026

Overview
Daily Dairy is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we handle your information.

Data Collection & Storage
Local Storage: All your diary entries, including text, images, tags, and mood data, are stored locally on your device using an encrypted-ready database (Hive). We do not have access to your personal journal entries.
No Cloud Sync: Currently, Daily Dairy does not sync your data to any external servers or cloud services. Your data stays with you.
Biometrics: If you enable biometric lock (Fingerprint/FaceID), the authentication is handled entirely by your device's secure hardware. We do not store or transmit your biometric data.
Third-Party Services
Advertising: We use Google AdMob to display ads. AdMob may collect and use certain data (such as your device's advertising ID) to show personalized ads. Please refer to Google’s Privacy Policy for more details.
Analytics: We may use anonymized crash reporting to improve app stability.
Data Security
Since your data is stored locally, the security of your entries depends on the security of your device. We recommend using the built-in PIN or Biometric lock feature for added protection.

